Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of an approximate inference algorithm for Statistical Relational Models (SRMs), which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications. The algorithm involves lifting over redundant message computations, which is a technique used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and data mining (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of factor graphs, which are commonly used in probabilistic graphical models (cs.DB).
